1
00:00:01,043 --> 00:00:03,795
(GASPING AND SCREAMING)

2
00:00:05,589 --> 00:00:09,343
-What the hell is he doing?
-The controls aren't working.

3
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:12,346
I don't know where we're going,
but my old hand's very excited about it.

4
00:00:12,429 --> 00:00:14,973
I thought that was just some
freaky alien thing.

5
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:17,184
-Are you sure that it's yours?
-Well...

6
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:23,106
-It got cut off. He grew a new one.
-You are completely impossible.

7
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:26,610
I'm not impossible. Just a bit unlikely.

8
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:28,570
(SCREAMING)

9
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:48,173
-Why did the Tardis bring us here?
-Oh, I love this bit.

10
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:52,261
-I thought you wanted to go home.
-I know, but all the same...

11
00:00:52,803 --> 00:00:55,097
-It's that feeling you get.
-Like you swallowed a hamster.

12
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,224
SOLDIER: Don't move. Stay where you are!

13
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:59,017
-Drop your weapons!
-We're not armed.

14
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:01,353
Look, no weapons,
never any weapons. We're safe.

15
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:06,066
-Look at their hands. They're clean.
-All right, process them. Him first.

16
00:01:07,526 --> 00:01:11,321
Wait! Oi! What's wrong with clean hands?

17
00:01:11,405 --> 00:01:12,823
MARTHA: What's going on?
Leave him alone.

18
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:14,283
(GRUNTING)

19
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:15,701
(MACHINE BUZZING)

20
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:17,828
Something tells me this isn't about
to check my blood pressure.

21
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:18,954
(SHOUTS)

22
00:01:19,037 --> 00:01:21,582
-What are you doing to him?
-Everyone gets processed.

23
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:23,292
It's taking a tissue sample.

24
00:01:23,375 --> 00:01:25,919
Ow, ow, ow, ow!

25
00:01:26,253 --> 00:01:29,881
An extrapolator here.
Some kind of accelerator?

26
00:01:30,007 --> 00:01:31,717
(MACHINE WHOOSHES)

27
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:37,055
-Are you all right?
-DOCTOR: I don't know.

28
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:39,099
That's...

29
00:01:52,279 --> 00:01:53,780
Arm yourself.

30
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:58,493
-MARTHA: Where did she come from?
-From me.

31
00:01:59,244 --> 00:02:01,913
-From you?
-How?

32
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:05,375
-Who is she?
-DOCTOR: Well, she's...

33
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:07,586
Well...

34
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,881
She's my daughter.

35
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:13,884
Hello, Dad.

36
00:02:15,636 --> 00:02:18,221
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

37
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:55,634
Are you primed to take orders,
ready to fight?

38
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:58,178
Instant mental download of all
strategic and military protocol, sir.

39
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:00,847
Generation 5000 soldier, primed
and in peak physical health.

40
00:03:00,931 --> 00:03:03,183
(COCKING GUN) Oh, I'm ready.

41
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:07,688
-Did you say daughter?
-Mmm. Technically.

42
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:09,106
Technically how?

43
00:03:09,231 --> 00:03:12,109
Progenation,
reproduction from a single organism.

44
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:14,986
It means one parent is biological
mother and father.

45
00:03:15,112 --> 00:03:17,280
You take a sample of diploid cells,
split them into haploids,

46
00:03:17,406 --> 00:03:20,701
then recombine them in
a different arrangement and grow,

47
00:03:20,784 --> 00:03:22,077
very quickly, apparently.

48
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,496
(CRASHING) Something's coming.

49
00:03:28,792 --> 00:03:31,920
-SOLDIER: It's the Hath!
-Get down!

50
00:03:39,261 --> 00:03:40,429
(GRUNTING)

51
00:03:40,512 --> 00:03:43,348
We have to blow the tunnel.
Get the detonator!

52
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:45,767
We're not detonating anything.

53
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:50,939
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

54
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:52,482
(GRUNTS)

55
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:57,779
SOLDIER: Grab it!

56
00:03:57,863 --> 00:04:00,365
-SOLDIER: Blow the thing!
-Martha!

57
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:01,783
No. Don't!

58
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,535
(ALARM BLARING)

59
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:26,433
You've sealed off the tunnel.
Why did you do that?

60
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:29,311
-They were trying to kill us.
-But they've got my friend.

61
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:31,021
Collateral damage.

62
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,064
At least you've still got her.
He lost both his men.

63
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:36,485
-I'd say you came out ahead.
-Her name is Martha.

64
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:39,362
And she's not collateral damage,
not for anyone.

65
00:04:39,446 --> 00:04:42,365
Have you got that, GI Jane?

66
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:46,411
-I'm gonna find her.
-(COCKING GUN) You're going nowhere.

67
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:50,749
You don't make sense, you two.
No guns, no marks, no fight in you.

68
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,836
I'm taking you to General Cobb.
Now move.

69
00:04:58,089 --> 00:04:59,716
(COUGHING)

70
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:16,358
(CREATURE GURGLING)

71
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:23,406
Hold on. I've got you.
Is it your arm, yeah?

72
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:25,242
(CREATURE MOANING)

73
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,202
Is that a yes?

74
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:29,079
(MOANS)

75
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:32,123
Let me examine it. Keep still.

76
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:34,459
Still, yeah?

77
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:36,962
No move.

78
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:43,051
Half fish, half human.

79
00:05:43,802 --> 00:05:47,180
How am I supposed to know?
Is that a shoulder?

80
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:51,643
Feels like a shoulder.
I think it's dislocated.

81
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:53,228
(DOOR OPENS)

82
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:59,025
I'm trying to help him.

83
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:04,364
I am a doctor and he is my patient.
And I'm not leaving him.

84
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:05,949
(GURGLING)

85
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:10,453
Now this is gonna hurt.

86
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:15,458
One, two, three!

87
00:06:15,917 --> 00:06:17,794
(GUNS COCKING)

88
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,297
(CREATURE GRUNTS)

89
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:34,144
Now then, I'm Dr Martha Jones.
Who the hell are you?

90
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:37,439
I'm Donna. What's your name?

91
00:06:38,023 --> 00:06:40,567
Don't know. It's not been assigned.

92
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,820
Well, if you don't know that,
what do you know?

93
00:06:44,696 --> 00:06:46,615
-How to fight.
-Nothing else?

94
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:50,869
The machine must embed military
history and tactics, but no name.

95
00:06:51,036 --> 00:06:55,248
-She's a generated anomaly.
-"Generated anomaly"?

96
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:57,751
Generated.

97
00:06:58,501 --> 00:07:00,921
Well, what about that? Jenny.

98
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:05,091
Jenny. Yeah. I like that. Jenny.

99
00:07:05,717 --> 00:07:09,596
-What do you think, Dad?
-Good as anything, I suppose.

100
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,181
You're not what you call
a natural parent, are you?

101
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:13,600
They stole a tissue sample at gunpoint
and processed it.

102
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:15,268
It's not what I'd call
natural parenting.

103
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:17,854
Rubbish. My friend Neris
fathered twins using a turkey baster.

104
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:19,022
It don't bother her.

105
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:21,358
Can I extrapolate a relationship
from a biological accident?

106
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:22,817
Uh, Child Support Agency can.

107
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:24,945
Look, just 'cause I share
certain physiological traits

108
00:07:25,028 --> 00:07:27,822
with simian primates doesn't make me
a monkey's uncle, does it?

109
00:07:27,906 --> 00:07:32,118
I'm not a monkey...or a child.

110
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:38,750
-So where are we? What planet's this?
-Messaline. Well, what's left of it.

111
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:43,088
MAN ON PA: 6-6-3, 75 deceased.

112
00:07:44,506 --> 00:07:48,677
Generation 6-6-7-1 extinct.

113
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:52,806
Generation 6-6-7-2,

114
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,225
46 deceased.

115
00:07:56,226 --> 00:07:58,895
Generation 6-6-8-0,

116
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:01,606
14 deceased.

117
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:04,275
Generation 6...

118
00:08:04,359 --> 00:08:07,988
-This is a theatre.
-Maybe they're doing Miss Saigon.

119
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:12,409
It's like a town or a city underground.

120
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:15,203
-But why?
-General Cobb, I presume.

121
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:18,915
Found in the western tunnels, I'm told,
with no marks.

122
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,667
There was an outbreak of pacifism

123
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:24,754
in the eastern zone, three generations
back, before we lost contact.

124
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:26,339
Is that where you came from?

125
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:29,926
Eastern zone, that's us. Yeah, yeah.
I'm the Doctor. This is Donna.

126
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:31,094
And I'm Jenny.

127
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:34,014
Don't think you can infect us
with your peacemaking.

128
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:36,099
We're committed to the fight
to the very end.

129
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:39,019
Well, that's all right. I can't stay
anyway. I gotta go and find my friend.

130
00:08:39,144 --> 00:08:40,937
That's not possible.
All movement is regulated.

131
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:44,482
-We're at war.
-Yes. I noticed. With the Hath.

132
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:47,819
But tell me,
"cause we got a bit out of circulation,

133
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:51,573
eastern zone and all that,
so who exactly are the Hath?

134
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:07,464
(CREATURE GRUNTS)

135
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,473
(ALL GURGLING)

136
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,070
COBB: Back at the dawn of this planet,

137
00:09:30,153 --> 00:09:33,782
these ancient halls
were carved from the earth.

138
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:36,826
Our ancestors dreamt of a new beginning,

139
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:41,164
a colony where human and Hath
work and live together.

140
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:43,291
What happened?

141
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:47,212
The dream died,
broken along with Hath promises.

142
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:49,422
They wanted it all for themselves.

143
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:51,591
But those early pioneers,
they fought back.

144
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:55,553
They used the machines to produce
soldiers instead of colonists

145
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:58,056
and began this battle for survival.

146
00:09:58,181 --> 00:10:01,267
There's nothing but earth outside.
Why is that?

147
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:04,395
-Why build everything underground?
-The surface is too dangerous.

148
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:07,023
Well, then why build windows
in the first place?

149
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:11,277
-And what's this mean?
-The rites and symbols of our ancestors.

150
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:13,947
The meanings lost in time.

151
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:17,408
-How long has this war gone on for?
-Longer than anyone can remember.

152
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:21,204
Countless generations
marked only by the dead.

153
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:24,457
-What, fighting all this time?
-Because we must.

154
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:27,961
Every child of the machine
is born with this knowledge.

155
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:30,880
It's our inheritance. It's all we know.

156
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:34,092
How to fight and how to die.

157
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:46,020
(MUTTERING AND GURGLING)

158
00:10:47,522 --> 00:10:51,734
Right. So we're here?

159
00:10:52,569 --> 00:10:54,237
(SIGHING)

160
00:10:56,865 --> 00:10:59,284
Does this show the entire city,
including the Hath side?

161
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,702
Yes. Why?

162
00:11:01,411 --> 00:11:05,415
-Well, it'll help us find Martha.
-We've more important things to do.

163
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:08,585
The progenation machines are powered
down for the night shift,

164
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,546
but, as soon as they're active, we could
breed a whole platoon from you two.

165
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:14,424
I'm not having sons and daughters
by some great big flipping machine.

166
00:11:14,549 --> 00:11:17,886
Sorry, no offence, but you're not...
Well, I mean, you're not real.

167
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:20,221
(SCOFFS) You're no better than him.

168
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:23,433
I have a body, I have a mind,
I have independent thought.

169
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:26,603
How am I not real?
What makes you better than me?

170
00:11:26,728 --> 00:11:29,522
Well said, soldier.
We need more like you

171
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:31,274
if ever we're to find the source.

172
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:34,277
Ooh, the source. What's that then?
What's the source?

173
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,822
-I like a source. What is it?
-The breath of life.

174
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:39,157
And that would be?

175
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,660
In the beginning, the Great One
breathed life into the universe.

176
00:11:42,744 --> 00:11:46,039
And then she looked at what she'd done
and she sighed.

177
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:49,375
-"She," I like that.
-Right, so it's a creation myth.

178
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:51,544
It's not myth, it's real.

179
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:57,717
That sigh, from the beginning of time,
it was caught and kept as the source.

180
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:01,346
It was lost when the war started,
but it's here somewhere.

181
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:04,224
Whoever holds the source
controls the destiny of this planet.

182
00:12:04,307 --> 00:12:07,810
Ah! I thought so.

183
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:09,854
There's a suppressed layer
of information in this map.

184
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,648
If I can just...

185
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:15,485
What is it? What does it mean?

186
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:18,947
See? A whole complex of tunnels
hidden from sight.

187
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,283
Hold on. Look!

188
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:27,413
That must be the lost temple.
The source will be inside.

189
00:12:27,497 --> 00:12:31,501
You've shown us the way.
And look, we're closer than the Hath.

190
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:32,669
It's ours.

191
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:36,297
That's a new map.
There's a different set of tunnels.

192
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,926
Tell them to prepare to move out.

193
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:43,513
We'll progenate new soldiers
on the morning shift, then we march.

194
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:47,183
Once we've reached the temple,
peace will be restored at long last.

195
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,519
Call me old-fashioned,
but if you really wanted peace,

196
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:53,022
-couldn't you just stop fighting?
-Only when we have the source.

197
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:56,276
It will give us the power
to erase every stinking Hath

198
00:12:56,359 --> 00:12:57,527
off the face of this planet.

199
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:59,904
Hang on, hang on.
A second ago, it was peace in our time,

200
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:03,157
-now you're talking about genocide.
-For us, that means the same thing.

201
00:13:03,241 --> 00:13:05,034
Then you need to get yourself
a better dictionary.

202
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:06,744
When you do, look up genocide.

203
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:09,205
You'll see a little picture of me there
and the caption will read,

204
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:11,124
"Over my dead body!"

205
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,335
You're the one who showed us
the path to victory,

206
00:13:14,419 --> 00:13:17,839
but you can consider the irony
from your prison cell.

207
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:19,632
Cline, at arms.

208
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:22,260
Oi, oi, oi. All right.
Cool the beans, Rambo.

209
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:24,429
COBB: Take them.
I won't have them spreading treason.

210
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:27,974
And if you try anything, Doctor,
I'll see that your woman dies first.

211
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:29,892
-We're not a couple.
-I'm not his woman.

212
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:31,185
Come on, this way.

213
00:13:31,269 --> 00:13:33,271
I'm gonna stop you, Cobb.
You need to know that.

214
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:36,524
I have an army and the breath
of God on my side, Doctor.

215
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:38,484
-What'll you have?
-This.

216
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:42,280
-Lock 'em up and guard 'em.
-What about the new soldier?

217
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:45,533
We can't trust her. She's from
pacifist stock. Take them all.

218
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:47,952
(LOUD GURGLING)

219
00:13:49,871 --> 00:13:51,956
But I didn't do anything.

220
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,463
(GRUNTS)

221
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:02,091
I think I just started a war.

222
00:14:08,723 --> 00:14:12,268
More numbers.
They've got to mean something.

223
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:15,313
Makes as much sense as
the breath of life story.

224
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:20,026
-You mean that's not true?
-No. It's a myth, isn't it, Doctor?

225
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:23,529
Yes, but there could still
be something real in that temple.

226
00:14:23,613 --> 00:14:27,116
Something that's become a myth,
a piece of technology, a weapon.

227
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,701
So the source could be a weapon

228
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:31,662
and we've just given directions
to Captain Nut job?

229
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:33,790
-Oh, yes.
-Not good, is it?

230
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,291
That's why we need to get out of here,

231
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:38,878
find Martha and stop Cobb
from slaughtering the Hath.

232
00:14:40,171 --> 00:14:42,382
(STAMMERING) What are you staring at?

233
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,717
You keep insisting you're not a soldier,

234
00:14:44,801 --> 00:14:48,513
but look at you, drawing up strategies
like a proper general.

235
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,890
No, no. I'm trying to stop the fighting.

236
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:54,519
-Isn't every soldier?
-Well, I suppose, but that's...

237
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:58,272
That's... Technically.
I haven't got time for this.

238
00:14:58,356 --> 00:14:59,857
Donna, give me your phone.
Time for an upgrade.

239
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:01,859
-And now you've got a weapon.
-It's not a weapon.

240
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:04,487
But you're using it to fight back.

241
00:15:04,946 --> 00:15:08,741
I'm gonna learn so much from you.
You are such a soldier.

242
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:12,620
-Donna, will you tell her?
-Ooh, you are speechless.

243
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,539
I'm loving this. You keep on, Jenny.

244
00:15:14,622 --> 00:15:16,290
(MOBILE RINGING)

245
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:19,836
-Doctor?
-Martha, you're alive!

246
00:15:19,961 --> 00:15:22,338
Doctor! Oh, am I glad
to hear your voice.

247
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:23,714
-Are you all right?
-I'm with Donna. We're fine.

248
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:26,926
-What about you?
-And... And Jenny. She's fine, too.

249
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,803
Yes, all right. And... And...

250
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:32,473
Jenny. That's the woman
from the machine, the soldier.

251
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:35,768
My daughter. Except she isn't, she's...

252
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:38,229
-Anyway, where are you?
-I'm in the Hath camp.

253
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:42,608
I'm okay, but something's going on.
The Hath are all marching off

254
00:15:42,692 --> 00:15:45,945
to some place that's
appeared on this map thing.

255
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:48,281
Oh. That was me.

256
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:51,701
If both armies are heading that way,
there's gonna be a bloodbath.

257
00:15:51,826 --> 00:15:53,286
-What do you want me to do?
-Just stay where you are.

258
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:54,787
If you're safe there,
don't move, do you hear?

259
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:55,913
But I can help.

260
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:58,708
(BUSY SIGNAL BEEPING) Doctor? Doctor?

261
00:16:01,294 --> 00:16:04,213
The doors that have been closed
will be open to us now.

262
00:16:04,297 --> 00:16:08,384
The door to the temple,
to the source and to victory.

263
00:16:14,182 --> 00:16:17,351
COBB: Come the dawn cycle, we march!

264
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,271
ALL: To war with the Hath!

265
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:25,318
They're getting ready to move out.
We have to get past that guard.

266
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:26,903
-I can deal with him.
-No, no, no, no.

267
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:28,404
-You're not going anywhere.
-What?

268
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:31,908
-You belong here with them.
-She belongs with us.

269
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:34,076
With you. She's your daughter.

270
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:36,245
She's a soldier.
She came out of that machine.

271
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:40,416
Oh, yes. I know that bit.
Listen, have you got that stethoscope?

272
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:43,878
Give it to me. Come on.

273
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:46,297
(DOCTOR SIGHING)

274
00:16:48,216 --> 00:16:50,801
-What are you doing?
-It's all right.

275
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,762
Just hold still.

276
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:02,313
Come here.

277
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:06,275
Listen, and then tell me
where she belongs.

278
00:17:07,944 --> 00:17:10,196
(HEART BEATING)

279
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:17,745
(MORE BEATING)

280
00:17:29,382 --> 00:17:30,758
Two hearts.

281
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:32,635
-DONNA: Exactly.
-What's going on?

282
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:37,431
Does that mean she's a...
What do you call a female Time Lord?

283
00:17:37,515 --> 00:17:40,476
-What's a Time Lord?
-It's who I am. It's where I'm from.

284
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:41,769
And I'm from you?

285
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:45,481
You're an echo, that's all.
A Time Lord is so much more.

286
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:50,695
A sum of knowledge, a code,
a shared history, a shared suffering.

287
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,616
And it's gone now, all of it.

288
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,413
Gone forever.

289
00:18:01,289 --> 00:18:02,832
What happened?

290
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:08,296
-There was a war.
-Like this one?

291
00:18:11,549 --> 00:18:13,384
Bigger. Much bigger.

292
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:15,678
And you fought?

293
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:18,180
And killed?

294
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:22,435
Yes.

295
00:18:24,437 --> 00:18:26,564
Then how are we different?

296
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:35,031
I need to charge it up. I need power.
Do you understand?

297
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:37,533
(GURGLING)

298
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:42,538
There's even more.
In 3D! Oh, you're a clever Hath!

299
00:18:43,456 --> 00:18:45,207
So this is where everybody's headed?

300
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:46,459
(HATH GURGLING)

301
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,086
But look, those tunnels sort of zig-zag.

302
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:53,049
If I went up and over the surface
in a straight line, I'd get there first.

303
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:54,842
Why not?

304
00:18:56,385 --> 00:19:01,182
Are these the readings for the surface?
But it doesn't look too bad.

305
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:03,684
Nitrogen and oxygen about 80-20.

306
00:19:03,768 --> 00:19:08,481
That's fine. Ozone levels are high
and some big radiation spikes.

307
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:11,567
But as long as
I'm not out there too long...

308
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:14,070
I have to find my friends.

309
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:21,285
Come on, then.

310
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:25,623
Hey.

311
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,918
I'm not supposed to talk to you.
I'm on duty.

312
00:19:29,043 --> 00:19:31,420
Yeah, I know. Guarding me.

313
00:19:32,046 --> 00:19:36,300
So does that mean I'm dangerous

314
00:19:36,759 --> 00:19:38,844
or that I need protecting?

315
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:43,391
-Protecting from what?
-Ooh, I don't know. Men like you.

316
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:53,192
Keep quiet and open the door.

317
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:59,281
I'd like to see you try that.

318
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:08,958
(WHISPERING) That's the way out.

319
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,293
Don't you dare.

320
00:20:13,254 --> 00:20:15,297
Let me distract this one.

321
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:20,970
I have picked up a few
womanly wiles over the years.

322
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:24,932
Let's save your wiles for later,

323
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:28,018
in case of emergency.

324
00:20:34,817 --> 00:20:37,486
(SQUEAKING)

325
00:20:49,707 --> 00:20:52,168
I was gonna distract him,
not clobber him.

326
00:20:52,293 --> 00:20:54,670
Well, it worked, didn't it?

327
00:20:55,171 --> 00:20:59,049
I still have a copy of that new map.
Just stay there. Don't hurt anyone.

328
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:00,551
(MOUSE SQUEAKING)

329
00:21:05,473 --> 00:21:07,349
(EXCLAIMS)

330
00:21:25,576 --> 00:21:27,036
(GURGLING)

331
00:21:27,161 --> 00:21:29,747
You can stay down here and
live your whole life in the shadows

332
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:32,208
or come with me and
stand in the open air,

333
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,668
feel the wind on your face.

334
00:21:34,835 --> 00:21:36,629
What's it gonna be?

335
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:37,963
(MOANING)

336
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:41,050
It's up to you,
but nothing's gonna stop me.

337
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:49,934
(GRUNTING)

338
00:21:53,062 --> 00:21:54,730
(EXCLAIMS)

339
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:58,567
(GASPING)

340
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:19,672
I knew you couldn't resist it.

341
00:22:19,755 --> 00:22:21,549
(GURGLING)

342
00:22:21,632 --> 00:22:23,008
Er, language!

343
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:25,719
Come on.

344
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:38,315
It was the girl. She tricked me.
They... They got away. I'm sorry.

345
00:22:38,399 --> 00:22:41,360
I've waited all my life for this moment.

346
00:22:41,485 --> 00:22:45,823
No one's gonna get in my way,
certainly not this Doctor.

347
00:22:46,615 --> 00:22:49,410
Alarm! We march!

348
00:22:49,493 --> 00:22:51,245
To war!

349
00:22:51,787 --> 00:22:52,997
Wait!

350
00:22:54,123 --> 00:22:57,042
This is it. The hidden tunnel.

351
00:22:57,668 --> 00:22:59,378
There must be a control panel.

352
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:02,756
There's another one of those numbers.
They're everywhere.

353
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,425
DOCTOR: The original builders
must have left them.

354
00:23:04,508 --> 00:23:06,552
An old cataloguing system.

355
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,929
You got a pen, a bit of paper?

356
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:12,266
'Cause, do you see?
The numbers are counting down.

357
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:16,687
This one ends in 1-4.
The prison cell said 1-6.

358
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:19,315
Always thinking, both of you.
Who are you people?

359
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:22,234
-I told you, I'm the Doctor.
-The Doctor, that's it?

360
00:23:22,318 --> 00:23:25,738
-That's all he ever says.
-So you don't have a name either?

361
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,365
-Are you an anomaly, too?
-No.

362
00:23:28,991 --> 00:23:31,785
Oh, come off it. You're the most
anomalous bloke I've ever known.

363
00:23:31,869 --> 00:23:33,162
Here it is!

364
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:35,748
And Time Lords,
what are they for exactly?

365
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:38,834
For? They're not...
They're not for anything.

366
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:43,547
-So what do you do?
-I travel through time and space.

367
00:23:43,631 --> 00:23:46,675
He saves planets, rescues civilisations

368
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:50,095
defeats terrible creatures
and runs a lot.

369
00:23:50,304 --> 00:23:53,849
Seriously, there's an outrageous amount
of running involved.

370
00:23:53,974 --> 00:23:55,392
Great!

371
00:23:55,935 --> 00:23:57,603
COBB: Support 5, with me.

372
00:23:57,686 --> 00:24:00,773
No. What were you saying about running?

373
00:24:14,203 --> 00:24:16,580
That's not mood lighting, is it?

374
00:24:22,002 --> 00:24:25,172
-No. I didn't think so.
-Arming device.

375
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:31,053
There's more of these.

376
00:24:31,178 --> 00:24:34,014
Always eight numbers,
counting down the closer we get.

377
00:24:34,098 --> 00:24:35,140
(GRUNTS)

378
00:24:35,224 --> 00:24:36,392
Here we go.

379
00:24:36,475 --> 00:24:39,395
DONNA: You'd better be quick.
The general.

380
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:42,231
-Where are you going?
-I can hold them up.

381
00:24:42,314 --> 00:24:45,109
-No. We don't need any more dead.
-But it's them or us.

382
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:48,070
-It doesn't mean you have to kill them.
-I'm trying to save your life.

383
00:24:48,195 --> 00:24:50,572
Listen to me, the killing,

384
00:24:52,074 --> 00:24:56,161
after a while it infects you
and once it does you're never rid of it.

385
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:59,623
-But we don't have a choice.
-We always have a choice.

386
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:01,875
-I'm sorry.
-Jenny!

387
00:25:03,335 --> 00:25:05,379
SOLDIER: This door, now!

388
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:10,801
SOLDIER: Right, there she is! Come on!

389
00:25:17,182 --> 00:25:21,270
-Told you. Nothing but a soldier.
-She's trying to help.

390
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:28,068
You must increase your fire!

391
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:33,615
-DOCTOR: Jenny, come on!
-I'm coming.

392
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,161
Cease-fire! Cease-fire.

393
00:25:38,704 --> 00:25:41,457
-That's it.
-Jenny, leave it. Let's go!

394
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:46,170
COBB: You're a child of the machine.
You're on my side.

395
00:25:46,295 --> 00:25:50,674
Join us.
Join us in the war against the Hath.

396
00:25:50,758 --> 00:25:53,635
It's in your blood, girl. Don't deny it.

397
00:26:04,605 --> 00:26:06,190
Jenny, come on!

398
00:26:06,899 --> 00:26:08,984
-That's it!
-Hurry up!

399
00:26:09,860 --> 00:26:12,654
Oh, no, no, no, no.
The circuits moved back.

400
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:15,157
-Zap it back again!
-The controls are back there.

401
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:16,325
They're coming!

402
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:17,910
Wait! Just...

403
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:20,704
There isn't... Jenny, I can't...

404
00:26:20,788 --> 00:26:23,248
I'll have to manage on my own.

405
00:26:26,085 --> 00:26:28,295
Watch and learn, Father.

406
00:26:34,343 --> 00:26:36,553
No way.

407
00:26:39,348 --> 00:26:43,435
-But that was impossible.
-Not impossible. Just a bit unlikely.

408
00:26:43,519 --> 00:26:47,064
Brilliant. You were brilliant!
Brilliant!

409
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:50,109
I didn't kill him. General Cobb.
I could've killed him, but I didn't.

410
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,152
You were right. I had a choice.

411
00:26:52,236 --> 00:26:54,738
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

412
00:26:56,698 --> 00:26:58,325
I warned you, Cobb.

413
00:26:58,408 --> 00:27:00,953
If the source is a weapon,
I'm gonna make sure you never use it.

414
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:03,789
One of us is gonna die today
and it won't be me.

415
00:27:20,556 --> 00:27:22,975
It can't be much further.

416
00:27:23,142 --> 00:27:24,309
(PANTING)

417
00:27:24,393 --> 00:27:26,061
(SCREAMS)

418
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:29,398
(GURGLING)

419
00:27:33,569 --> 00:27:35,112
(COUGHING)

420
00:27:36,905 --> 00:27:38,448
Help me!

421
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:43,245
I'm sinking! I'm sinking! Help me peg!

422
00:27:43,579 --> 00:27:46,039
Help me! Help me! Help me peg!

423
00:27:46,415 --> 00:27:48,375
Help! I'm sinking!

424
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:50,127
(CRYING)

425
00:28:06,602 --> 00:28:08,061
(GRUNTING)

426
00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:13,567
(MOANING AND GURGLING)

427
00:28:13,650 --> 00:28:14,776
No!

428
00:28:19,948 --> 00:28:21,658
No!

429
00:28:47,809 --> 00:28:51,647
So you travel together,
but you're not together.

430
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:56,902
What? No, no, no way.
No, no. We're friends, that's all.

431
00:28:57,611 --> 00:29:01,782
I mean, we're not even the same species.
There's probably laws against it.

432
00:29:01,907 --> 00:29:05,327
-And what's it like, the travelling?
-Oh, never a dull moment.

433
00:29:05,452 --> 00:29:07,955
It can be terrifying,

434
00:29:08,038 --> 00:29:10,749
brilliant and funny,
sometimes all at the same time.

435
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:14,920
I've seen some amazing things though.
A whole new world.

436
00:29:15,379 --> 00:29:18,507
-Oh, I'd love to see new worlds.
-You will.

437
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:21,510
-Won't she, Doctor?
-Hmm?

438
00:29:21,718 --> 00:29:24,680
Do you think Jenny
will see any new worlds?

439
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:27,266
I suppose so.

440
00:29:28,684 --> 00:29:31,895
You mean...
You mean you'll take me with you?

441
00:29:31,979 --> 00:29:33,188
Well, we can't leave you here, can we?

442
00:29:33,272 --> 00:29:36,275
Oh, thank you, thank you, thank you!

443
00:29:36,358 --> 00:29:40,112
-Come on. Let's get a move on.
-Careful, there might be traps.

444
00:29:40,195 --> 00:29:42,823
Kids, they never listen.

445
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:51,748
Oh, I know that look.
See it a lot round our way.

446
00:29:51,873 --> 00:29:56,128
Blokes with pushchairs and frowns.
You've got dad shock.

447
00:29:56,211 --> 00:29:58,964
-Dad shock?
-Sudden, unexpected fatherhood.

448
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:01,383
-It'll take a bit of getting used to.
-No. It's not that.

449
00:30:01,508 --> 00:30:05,137
Well, what is it then?
Having Jenny in the Tardis, is that it?

450
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:07,347
What's she gonna do? Cramp your style?

451
00:30:07,431 --> 00:30:11,768
Like, you've got a sports car, she's
gonna turn it into a people carrier?

452
00:30:11,852 --> 00:30:13,353
Donna, I've been a father before.

453
00:30:13,437 --> 00:30:16,356
-What?
-I lost all that a long time ago,

454
00:30:16,898 --> 00:30:21,320
-along with everything else.
-I'm sorry. I didn't know.

455
00:30:23,572 --> 00:30:25,907
Why didn't you tell me?

456
00:30:26,742 --> 00:30:29,745
You talk all the time,
but you don't say anything.

457
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:31,538
I know. Just...

458
00:30:34,541 --> 00:30:37,377
When I look at her now, I can see them,

459
00:30:39,087 --> 00:30:42,299
the hole they left,
all the pain that filled it.

460
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:48,055
Just don't know
if I can face that every day.

461
00:30:48,138 --> 00:30:53,101
It won't stay like that.
She'll help you. We both will.

462
00:30:53,935 --> 00:30:57,105
When they died,
that part of me died with them.

463
00:30:58,648 --> 00:31:01,068
It'll never come back, not now.

464
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:07,908
I'll tell you something, Doctor,
something I've never told you before.

465
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:11,787
I think you're wrong.

466
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,872
(LASERS BLASTING)

467
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:17,125
They've blasted through the beams.
Time to run again.

468
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:20,587
-Love the running. Yeah?
-Love the running.

469
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:27,135
(MARTHA CRYING)

470
00:31:44,653 --> 00:31:46,279
(GUNS FIRING)

471
00:31:46,738 --> 00:31:48,281
-DONNA: We're trapped.
-Can't be.

472
00:31:48,365 --> 00:31:52,369
This must be the temple. This is a door.

473
00:31:52,494 --> 00:31:53,912
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

474
00:31:53,995 --> 00:31:57,457
And again. We're down to 1-2 now.

475
00:31:57,541 --> 00:31:59,126
-I got it!
-I can hear them.

476
00:31:59,209 --> 00:32:01,378
-Nearly done!
-This can't be a cataloguing system.

477
00:32:01,503 --> 00:32:02,546
They're getting closer.

478
00:32:02,629 --> 00:32:04,339
-Then get back here.
-They're too similar.

479
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:05,507
-JENNY: Not yet.
-Too familiar.

480
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:06,716
Now!

481
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:09,136
Got it!

482
00:32:16,852 --> 00:32:18,437
They're coming.

483
00:32:19,729 --> 00:32:21,857
Close the door.

484
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:24,734
-That was close.
-No fun otherwise.

485
00:32:31,366 --> 00:32:33,618
It's not what I'd call a temple.

486
00:32:33,702 --> 00:32:37,038
-It looks more like...
-Fusion-drive transport.

487
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:40,709
-It's a spaceship.
-What, the original one?

488
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:42,294
The one the first colonists arrived on?

489
00:32:42,377 --> 00:32:46,131
Well, it could be, but the power cells
would have run down after all that time.

490
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:47,591
This one's still powered up
and functioning.

491
00:32:47,716 --> 00:32:48,967
Come on!

492
00:32:57,142 --> 00:32:59,936
It's the Hath.
That door's not gonna last much longer.

493
00:33:00,061 --> 00:33:02,856
And if General Cobb gets through
down there, war's gonna break out.

494
00:33:02,939 --> 00:33:04,941
Look, look, look, look!

495
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:07,110
Ship's log.

496
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:09,988
First wave of human-Hath
co-colonisation of Planet Messaline.

497
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:11,239
So it is the original ship?

498
00:33:11,364 --> 00:33:13,658
-What happened?
-There's one construction.

499
00:33:13,742 --> 00:33:16,286
They used robot drones
to build the city.

500
00:33:16,411 --> 00:33:19,873
-But does it mention the war?
-DOCTOR: Final entry,

501
00:33:19,956 --> 00:33:21,708
"Mission commander dead.

502
00:33:21,791 --> 00:33:23,627
"Still no agreement on who
should assume leadership.

503
00:33:23,752 --> 00:33:25,712
"Hath and humans
have divided into factions."

504
00:33:25,795 --> 00:33:28,465
That must be it. A power vacuum.

505
00:33:28,590 --> 00:33:30,926
The crew divided into two factions,
then turned on each other.

506
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:33,303
Start using the progenation machines,
suddenly you've got two armies

507
00:33:33,428 --> 00:33:34,554
fighting a never-ending war.

508
00:33:34,638 --> 00:33:36,598
Two armies who are now both outside.

509
00:33:36,681 --> 00:33:38,225
Look at that!

510
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:42,687
-It's like the numbers in the tunnels.
-No, no, no, but listen.

511
00:33:42,771 --> 00:33:45,148
I spent six months working as a temp
in Hounslow Library

512
00:33:45,232 --> 00:33:48,109
and I mastered the Dewey Decimal
System in two days flat.

513
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:51,947
I'm good with numbers.
It's staring us in the face.

514
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,323
What is?

515
00:33:54,449 --> 00:33:55,951
It's the date.

516
00:33:57,786 --> 00:34:00,205
Assuming the first two numbers
are some big old space date,

517
00:34:00,288 --> 00:34:02,332
then you've got year, month, day.

518
00:34:02,415 --> 00:34:03,917
It's the other way round,
like it is in America.

519
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,628
Oh, it's the new Byzantine calendar!

520
00:34:07,212 --> 00:34:10,465
The codes are completion dates
for each section.

521
00:34:10,924 --> 00:34:13,510
They finish it, they stamp the date on.

522
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:15,971
So the numbers aren't counting down.

523
00:34:16,054 --> 00:34:20,559
They're going out from here day by day
as the city got built.

524
00:34:20,642 --> 00:34:23,186
Yes. Oh, good work, Donna!

525
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:25,730
Yeah, but you're still not getting it.

526
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:29,568
The first number I saw back there
was 60-12-07-17.

527
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:34,990
-Well, look at the date today.
-0-7-24... No.

528
00:34:35,407 --> 00:34:37,784
-What does it mean?
-Seven days.

529
00:34:37,867 --> 00:34:39,202
That's it!

530
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,413
-Seven days.
-Seven days.

531
00:34:41,496 --> 00:34:44,499
-What do you mean, "seven days"?
-Seven days since war broke out.

532
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:48,670
This war started seven days ago.
Just a week. A week.

533
00:34:48,753 --> 00:34:52,632
-They said years.
-No. They said generations.

534
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:55,468
And if they're all like you and
they're products of those machines...

535
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:57,304
They could have 20 generations in a day.

536
00:34:57,387 --> 00:34:59,598
Each generation gets killed in the war,
passes on the legend.

537
00:34:59,681 --> 00:35:01,600
Oh, Donna, you're a genius!

538
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:03,935
But all the buildings, the encampments,
they're in ruins.

539
00:35:04,019 --> 00:35:08,148
They're not ruined, they're just empty,
waiting to be populated.

540
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:11,443
Oh, they've mythologized
their entire history.

541
00:35:11,526 --> 00:35:14,738
The source must be part of that, too.
Come on!

542
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:20,702
-Doctor!
-Martha!

543
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:23,163
Oh, I should've known you wouldn't stay
away from all the excitement.

544
00:35:23,246 --> 00:35:25,957
-Donna'!
-Ooh, you're filthy. What happened?

545
00:35:26,041 --> 00:35:28,084
I took the surface route.

546
00:35:28,209 --> 00:35:29,377
(COBB SHOUTING)

547
00:35:29,461 --> 00:35:30,670
That's the General.
We haven't got much time.

548
00:35:30,754 --> 00:35:32,464
We don't even know
what we're looking for.

549
00:35:32,547 --> 00:35:35,425
-Is it me or can you smell flowers?
-Yes.

550
00:35:36,051 --> 00:35:37,636
Bougainvillea.

551
00:35:38,887 --> 00:35:40,805
I say we follow our nose.

552
00:35:40,889 --> 00:35:42,474
(COBB SHOUTING)

553
00:35:54,235 --> 00:35:55,487
Oh, yes!

554
00:35:58,573 --> 00:35:59,991
Yes!

555
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:05,205
Isn't this brilliant?

556
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:08,208
Is that the source?

557
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:10,752
It's beautiful.

558
00:36:11,086 --> 00:36:13,546
-What is it?
-Terraforming.

559
00:36:14,047 --> 00:36:17,050
It's a third-generation
terraforming device.

560
00:36:17,133 --> 00:36:20,637
-So why are we suddenly in Kew Gardens?
-'Cause that's what it does.

561
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:23,598
All this, only bigger, much bigger.
It's in a transit state.

562
00:36:23,682 --> 00:36:25,934
Producing all this must help
keep it stable before they find...

563
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:27,394
(CRASHING)

564
00:36:30,563 --> 00:36:34,109
Stop! Hold your fire!

565
00:36:34,567 --> 00:36:37,904
-What is this, some kind of trap?
-You said you wanted this war over.

566
00:36:37,987 --> 00:36:41,741
-I want this war won!
-You can't win. No one can.

567
00:36:41,950 --> 00:36:43,368
You don't even know why you're here.

568
00:36:43,451 --> 00:36:46,371
Your whole history,
it's just Chinese whispers,

569
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:49,541
getting more distorted
the more it's passed on.

570
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:53,002
This is the source.

571
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,505
This is what you're fighting over,

572
00:36:55,588 --> 00:36:58,633
a device to rejuvenate
a planet's ecosystem.

573
00:36:58,717 --> 00:36:59,968
It's nothing mystical.

574
00:37:00,051 --> 00:37:02,929
It's from a laboratory,
not some creator.

575
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:05,390
It's a bubble of gases,

576
00:37:06,141 --> 00:37:09,561
a cocktail of stuff
for accelerated evolution.

577
00:37:09,644 --> 00:37:12,897
Methane, hydrogen, ammonia,
amino acids, proteins, nucleic acids.

578
00:37:12,981 --> 00:37:15,984
It's used to make
barren planets habitable.

579
00:37:17,777 --> 00:37:19,446
Look around you.

580
00:37:20,155 --> 00:37:23,032
It's not for killing.
It's for bringing life.

581
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:29,164
If you allow it, it can lift you out
of these dark tunnels

582
00:37:29,664 --> 00:37:33,293
and into the bright, bright sunlight.

583
00:37:34,836 --> 00:37:37,672
No more fighting, no more killing.

584
00:37:40,884 --> 00:37:45,764
I'm the Doctor
and I declare this war is over.

585
00:38:26,846 --> 00:38:28,097
What's happening?

586
00:38:28,181 --> 00:38:32,018
The gases will escape and trigger
the terraforming process.

587
00:38:32,268 --> 00:38:35,230
-What does that mean?
-It means a new world.

588
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:38,149
No!

589
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:45,031
Jenny. Jenny. Talk to me, Jenny.

590
00:38:50,745 --> 00:38:52,872
Is she gonna be all right?

591
00:39:05,218 --> 00:39:06,678
A new world.

592
00:39:08,263 --> 00:39:09,848
It's beautiful.

593
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:15,019
Jenny, please hold on.
You need to hold on, do you hear me?

594
00:39:16,187 --> 00:39:19,607
We've got things to do,
you and me, eh? Eh?

595
00:39:22,277 --> 00:39:24,112
We can go anywhere.

596
00:39:25,530 --> 00:39:27,824
Everywhere. You choose.

597
00:39:28,783 --> 00:39:30,535
That sounds good.

598
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:37,375
You're my daughter
and we've only just got started.

599
00:39:40,003 --> 00:39:41,921
You're gonna be great.

600
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:46,134
You're gonna be more than great.

601
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:49,804
You're gonna be amazing.
Do you hear me, Jenny?

602
00:40:15,038 --> 00:40:16,789
Two hearts.

603
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,959
Two hearts, just like me.

604
00:40:21,169 --> 00:40:23,338
If we wait, we just wait...

605
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:26,549
There's no sign, Doctor.

606
00:40:27,008 --> 00:40:31,387
There's no regeneration.
She's like you, but maybe not enough.

607
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:34,974
No. Too much.

608
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:39,646
That's the truth of it.

609
00:40:40,521 --> 00:40:42,607
She was too much like me.

610
00:41:24,983 --> 00:41:26,526
I never would.

611
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:30,363
Have you got that?

612
00:41:31,239 --> 00:41:33,116
I never would.

613
00:41:38,538 --> 00:41:40,873
When you start this new world,

614
00:41:42,375 --> 00:41:44,669
this world of human and Hath,

615
00:41:46,629 --> 00:41:48,214
remember that!

616
00:41:50,383 --> 00:41:53,386
Make the foundation of this society

617
00:41:55,263 --> 00:41:57,140
a man who never would!

618
00:42:28,504 --> 00:42:31,924
It's happening. The terraforming.

619
00:42:32,759 --> 00:42:36,345
Build a city nice and safe underground,

620
00:42:36,471 --> 00:42:39,849
strip away the top soil and there it is.

621
00:42:41,809 --> 00:42:46,147
-And what about Jenny?
-Let us give her a proper ceremony.

622
00:42:47,315 --> 00:42:50,735
I think it would help us. Please.

623
00:42:58,284 --> 00:43:01,871
Jenny was the reason
for the Tardis bringing us here.

624
00:43:01,954 --> 00:43:04,040
It just got here too soon,

625
00:43:04,832 --> 00:43:07,835
which then created
Jenny in the first place.

626
00:43:09,879 --> 00:43:13,883
Paradox. An endless paradox.

627
00:43:18,262 --> 00:43:21,682
-Time to go home.
-Yeah. Home.

628
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:27,146
(TARDIS RUMBLING)

629
00:43:43,746 --> 00:43:47,166
-Are you sure about this?
-Yeah. Positive.

630
00:43:47,834 --> 00:43:51,838
I can't do this any more.
You'll be the same one day.

631
00:43:51,921 --> 00:43:54,298
Not me, never.

632
00:43:54,423 --> 00:43:58,427
How could I ever go back to
normal life after seeing all this?

633
00:43:59,554 --> 00:44:02,348
I'm gonna travel with that man forever.

634
00:44:09,438 --> 00:44:11,232
-Good luck.
-And you.

635
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:19,490
-We're making a habit of this.
-Yeah, and you'd think it'd get easier.

636
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:23,494
All those things you've
been ready to die for.

637
00:44:23,578 --> 00:44:25,246
I thought for a moment there

638
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:27,498
you'd finally found
something worth living for.

639
00:44:27,582 --> 00:44:31,169
Oh, there's always something
worth living for, Martha.

640
00:44:42,346 --> 00:44:46,434
-Bye, Doctor.
-Goodbye, Dr Jones.

641
00:45:27,058 --> 00:45:28,726
Hello, boys.

642
00:45:31,646 --> 00:45:33,481
(WHOOSHING)

643
00:45:34,148 --> 00:45:35,816
The shuttle.

644
00:45:37,193 --> 00:45:39,237
Jenny, what are you doing? Come back.

645
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:43,407
Sorry, can't stop.
What are you gonna do? Tell my dad?

646
00:45:43,491 --> 00:45:47,161
-But where are you going?
-I've got the whole universe.

647
00:45:47,703 --> 00:45:50,748
Planets to save,
civilisations to rescue,

648
00:45:51,082 --> 00:45:53,334
creatures to defeat

649
00:45:55,461 --> 00:45:58,005
and an awful lot of running to do.

650
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:03,302
(CAR HONKING)

651
00:46:03,427 --> 00:46:05,221
-Agatha Christie.
-What about her?

652
00:46:05,346 --> 00:46:07,223
-That's me.
-No!

653
00:46:07,890 --> 00:46:08,933
Murder!

654
00:46:09,016 --> 00:46:10,559
Chief Inspector Smith
from Scotland Yard,

655
00:46:10,643 --> 00:46:13,562
known as the Doctor. Miss Noble is
the plucky young girl that helps me out.

656
00:46:13,646 --> 00:46:14,981
I say.

657
00:46:15,356 --> 00:46:18,609
There's a murder, a mystery
and Agatha Christie.

658
00:46:19,068 --> 00:46:21,487
So? Happens to me all the time.

659
00:46:21,570 --> 00:46:23,406
Show yourself, demon.

660
00:46:23,489 --> 00:46:24,657
No!

661
00:46:24,740 --> 00:46:25,866
There's nowhere to run.

662
00:46:26,367 --> 00:46:28,744
The thrill is in the chase,
never in the capture.

663
00:46:28,869 --> 00:46:29,996
Oh, my God.

664
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:33,124
If anyone can solve this, it's you.

